A fire tore through a shopping mall in the Siberian city of Kemerovo, on Sunday. At least 37 people were killed and 69 are unaccounted for, according to Russian news agencies, citing local authorities. The TASS news agency reported more than 100 people had been evacuated from the shopping center, which contains cinemas, restaurants and shops. "At this time, we can confirm the deaths of 37 people in the fire at the Kemerovo shopping center,” Russia's Investigative Committee was quoted as saying by TASS. The fire reportedly spread across 1,000 square meters of the center The city of Kemerovo, a coal-mining center in Siberia lies 3,600 kilometers (2,200 miles) east of Moscow. Authorities said there was no immediate indication of the cause of the fire. Television coverage from the scene showed people jumping from the windows of the mall, which was engulfed in black smoke. Interfax news agency said the fire had spread across more than 1,000 square meters (10,760 square feet) of the center. av/aw /Reuters, AFP)